            <title>[THRIFT-2202] Delphi TServerImpl.DefaultLogDelegate may stop the server with I/O-Error 105</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2202</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the server process has no console window allocated or assigned, the Writeln() statement in TServerImpl.DefaultLogDelegate() causes an I/O-error 105. The resulting exception lets the server fail instantly when the first client connects to the server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
